    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan I've designed:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Stepper Compound Component\n\n### What Gets Created (12 total changes ã 0 existing files modified)\n\n**6 new component/example files:**\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | Main compound component (`@/lib/utils` for `cn`) |\n| `new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | 3-step horizontal wizard demo |\n| `bases/radix/ui/stepper.tsx` | Radix base version (different `cn` path) |\n| `bases/radix/examples/stepper-example.tsx` | Multi-variant radix example |\n| `bases/base/ui/stepper.tsx` | Base UI version |\n| `bases/base/examples/stepper-example.tsx` | Base UI example |\n\n**6 registry entries added** (append-only to `_registry.ts` files):\n- `new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` ã `{ name: \"stepper\", type: \"registry:ui\", ... }`\n- `new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` ã `{ name: \"stepper-demo\", registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"], ... }`\n- `bases/radix/ui/_registry.ts` ã stepper entry with `meta.links`\n- `bases/radix/examples/_registry.ts` ã `{ name: \"stepper-example\", title: \"Stepper\", registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\", \"card\", \"example\"], ... }`\n- Same for `bases/base/`\n\n---\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n**9 sub-components:** `Stepper` ôñ `StepperList` ôñ `StepperItem` ôñ `StepperTrigger` ôñ `StepperIndicator` ôñ `StepperTitle` ôñ `StepperDescription` ôñ `StepperSeparator` ôñ `StepperPanel`\n\n**2 React contexts** (like `Sidebar`):\n- `StepperContext` (root) ã `value`, `onValueChange`, `orientation`\n- `StepperItemContext` (per-item, set by `StepperList`) ã `isActive`, `isCompleted`, `isDisabled`, `index`\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- `StepperList` uses `React.Children.toArray()` to read child `value` props in order, auto-computes `isCompleted = index < activeIndex`, wraps each child in `StepperItemContext.Provider`\n- `StepperItem` destructures `value`/`completed`/`disabled` so they don't leak to the DOM\n- `StepperPanel` uses `hidden={!isActive}` to keep DOM mounted (important for forms)\n- `StepperIndicator` shows `<CheckIcon>` when completed, step number otherwise\n- Both controlled (`value` + `onValueChange`) and uncontrolled (`defaultValue`) modes supported\n- Orientation handled via `data-orientation` + Tailwind conditional classes ã same DOM structure for both orientations",
